chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have psychotic depression.
chunks.plain_content:
Psychotic depression and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have psychotic depression.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:

chunks.html_content:
Find out what you need to do if you have severe depression.

Fill in form M1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
